<div class="row">
    <div class="col-8">
        <h1 class="heading-xlarge">
            Access a DfE service
        </h1>

        <p>A DfE Sign-in account will allow you to access DfE online services for your organisation.</p>

        <h2 class="heading-medium">
            How do I add <%=locals.service.name%> to my account?
        </h2>
        <p>An approver at your organisation will be able to provide you with access to <%=locals.service.name%>.</p>
        <p>Services added to your account are listed on your DfE Sign-in <a href="<%=locals.urls.services%>/my-services">Services</a> page.</p>
        <p>If you are an approver you can add services to your account by selecting your name from the <a href="<%=locals.urls.services%>/approvals/users">Users</a> page and add services.</p>

        <h2 class="heading-medium">
            What is an approver?
        </h2>
        <p>An approver can invite users to DfE Sign-in, link users to an organisation and give access to services.</p>

        <h2 class="heading-medium">
            Find an approver
        </h2>
        <p>If you have a DfE Sign-in account, you can view your organisation approvers from the <a href="<%=locals.urls.services%>/organisations">Organisations</a> page and select the information and approvers link.</p>

        <h2 class="heading-medium">
            Become an approver
        </h2>

        <p>An existing approver can make a user an approver by accessing that individual's account from the <a href="<%=locals.urls.services%>/approvals/users">Users</a> page.</p>

        <h2 class="heading-medium">
            There are no approvers at my organisation
        </h2>
        <p>To set up the first approver at your organisation, you will need to send an email to the <a href="/contact/approver/new-approver">Service Team</a>.</p>

        <details>
            <summary><span class="summary">Still having problems?</span></summary>
            <div class="panel panel-border-narrow">
                <p>If you are still having problems, please <a href="/contact/submit?type=service-access&service=<%=locals.service.name%>">submit a support request</a>.</p>
            </div>
        </details>
    </div>
</div>
